document_notes.text:
This update for webkit2gtk3 fixes the following issues:

Add security patches (bsc#1211846):                                                            
                                                                                               
- CVE-2023-28204: Fixed processing of web content that may disclose sensitive information (bsc#1211659).
- CVE-2023-32373: Fixed processing of maliciously crafted web content that may lead to arbitrary code execution (bsc#1211658).

notes.text: An out-of-bounds read was addressed with improved input validation. This issue is fixed in watchOS 9.5, tvOS 16.5, macOS Ventura 13.4, iOS 15.7.6 and iPadOS 15.7.6, Safari 16.5, iOS 16.5 and iPadOS 16.5. Processing web content may disclose sensitive information. Apple is aware of a report that this issue may have been actively exploited.

notes.text: A use-after-free issue was addressed with improved memory management. This issue is fixed in watchOS 9.5, tvOS 16.5, macOS Ventura 13.4, iOS 15.7.6 and iPadOS 15.7.6, Safari 16.5, iOS 16.5 and iPadOS 16.5. Processing maliciously crafted web content may lead to arbitrary code execution. Apple is aware of a report that this issue may have been actively exploited.
